gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: NCEI Accession 0123645 contains oceanographic and surface meteorological data in netCDF formatted files, which follow the Climate and Forecast metadata convention (CF) and the Attribute Convention for Data Discovery (ACDD). University of Michigan collected the data from University of Michigan Marine Hydrodynamics Laboratories Bio Buoy, an in-situ moored station, in the Great Lakes. GLOS, which assembles data from University of Michigan and other sub-regional coastal and ocean observing systems of the Great Lakes region of the United States, submitted the data to NCEI as part of the Integrated Ocean Observing System Data Assembly Centers (IOOS DACs) Data Stewardship Program. Each month, NCEI adds to the Accession the data collected during the previous month.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: This is a vocabulary of the parameters used in IOOS. It has been developed, in coordination with SECOORA, the COARDS Climate-Forecast Standard Names, and input from the 11 Regional Associations in IOOS and the NOAA IOOS Program Office.

gmd:supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString:
The IOOS vocabulary of oceanographic and meteorological parameters is at http://mmisw.org/ont/ioos/parameter. The mapping of this vocabulary to the CF standard names vocabulary is at http://mmisw.org/ont/ioos/map_ioos_cf. The netCDF data files in the Accession use both vocabularies.
In this accession, NCEI has archived multiple versions of these data. The latest (and best) version of these data has the largest version number.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: NOAA created the National Centers for Environmental Information (NCEI) by merging NOAA's National Climatic Data Center (NCDC), National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC), and National Oceanographic Data Center (NODC), including the National Coastal Data Development Center (NCDDC), per the Consolidated and Further Continuing Appropriations Act, 2015, Public Law 113-235. NCEI launched publicly on April 22, 2015.
